      <div class="lwm-faq">
        <div class="lwm-faq-inner">
          <div class="lwm-section-heading">
            <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
            <p>Clear answers for people deciding whether LiveWithMS fits the kind of support they need.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="lwm-faq-grid">
            <article class="lwm-faq-item">
              <h3>Is LiveWithMS medical advice?</h3>
              <p class="lwm-faq-answer">No. LiveWithMS is designed for education, daily organization, reflection, and support. It does not replace medical advice or care from a qualified clinician.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="lwm-faq-item">
              <h3>Can I track symptoms and energy?</h3>
              <p class="lwm-faq-answer">Yes. You can track fatigue, pain, brain fog, mood, stress, sleep, hydration, and other day-to-day factors that may help you notice patterns over time.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="lwm-faq-item">
              <h3>Does the app help with difficult days?</h3>
              <p class="lwm-faq-answer">That is exactly what it is designed for. LiveWithMS combines check-ins, planning, Coach, nutrition support, routines, and calmer tools to help you decide what matters next.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="lwm-faq-item">
              <h3>Is there support beyond tracking?</h3>
              <p class="lwm-faq-answer">Yes. Alongside tracking, the app includes AI-guided reflection, nutrition support, short cognitive exercises, practical tools, care organization, and community support.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="lwm-faq-item">
              <h3>Can I use it if I’m newly diagnosed?</h3>
              <p class="lwm-faq-answer">Yes. Whether you are newly diagnosed or have been living with MS for years, the app is designed to help you stay organized and supported in everyday life.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="lwm-faq-item">
              <h3>What kind of access do I start with?</h3>
              <p class="lwm-faq-answer">LiveWithMS is a subscription app with full access and trial-based onboarding, so you can explore the complete experience rather than a cut-down version.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lwm-final-cta">
